<item>
            <title>[LU-19776] add partial addition/removal of an LQA range</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19776</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the recent LQA implementation it is not possible to add or remove the partial range.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lctl lqa add --fsname testfs --name lqa1 500-1000 ==&amp;gt; success
lctl lqa add --fsname testfs --name lqa1 500-700  ==&amp;gt; will return error
lctl lqa remove --fsname testfs --name lqa1 500-600 ==&amp;gt; error
lctl lqa remove --fsname testfs --name lqa1 500-1000 ==&amp;gt; success&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adding this capability would be useful for real-world usability.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
